Reasoning: The paper deals with the reconstruction of networks from motifs, which is a problem in network science. The paper also introduces a new definition of weak isomorphism and a distance metric on the space of all networks, which are topics related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the completeness, compactness, curves, and geodesics of the space of networks, which are topics related to statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the skeleta of networks, which are structures related to network analysis (cs.NI).
